		<title><![CDATA[Trying to recover block in editor as author]]></title>
		<link>http://wp-engine-bio-box.local/trying-to-recover-block-in-editor-as-author/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 27 Sep 2022 14:13:35 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Author]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://wp-engine-bio-box.local/?p=15</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Test to see if you can attempt to validate the block in the editor and it works.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Instructions</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Created a new post</li><li>Added bio block </li><li>Received the following error, again</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:quote -->
<blockquote class="wp-block-quote"><p>Error:&nbsp;Sorry, you are not allowed to filter users by role.</p><cite>from the block editor on this post... now we're gonna try to Publish it, go back to the editor and fix the errors in the block and see if that works </cite></blockquote>
<!-- /wp:quote -->

<!-- wp:wpenginebio/wpenginebio {"isLoaded":true,"user":{"id":5,"name":"Arthur McAuthor","url":"","description":"Just an everyday WordPress writer","link":"http://wp-engine-bio-box.local/author/author/","slug":"author","avatar_urls":{"24":"http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/59baf90179ecbb9559e97d2371ed2a0b?s=24\u0026amp;d=mm\u0026amp;r=g","48":"http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/59baf90179ecbb9559e97d2371ed2a0b?s=48\u0026amp;d=mm\u0026amp;r=g","96":"http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/59baf90179ecbb9559e97d2371ed2a0b?s=96\u0026amp;d=mm\u0026amp;r=g"},"meta":[],"user_email":"author@wpengine.com","_links":{"self":[{"href":"http://wp-engine-bio-box.local/wp-json/wp/v2/users/5"}],"collection":[{"href":"http://wp-engine-bio-box.local/wp-json/wp/v2/users"}]}}} -->
<div class="wp-block-wpenginebio-wpenginebio"><img alt="Gravatar for author@wpengine.com" src="//www.gravatar.com/avatar/59baf90179ecbb9559e97d2371ed2a0b?d=retro&amp;r=g&amp;s=150" height="150" width="150" class="react-gravatar" /><h2>Arthur McAuthor</h2><p>Just an everyday WordPress writer</p></div>
<!-- /wp:wpenginebio/wpenginebio -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":18,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="http://wp-engine-bio-box.local/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-1024x364.png" alt="" class="wp-image-18" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This experience could be improved by better handling responses from the REST API in the Block Editor. I'm not 100% sure this was available when I was working on this coding challenge, because I don't recall ever seeing the rest_user_cannot_view error when working on this. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The problem when I was working on this challenge was that the block just keep invalidating but would work on the front-end. I didn't realize this was because my code was trying to access other users' profile info, and as an Author that can't happen. Only Administrators can access the full User REST API endpoint for <em>all</em> users.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->]]></content:encoded>
